  "finger_focus": "Left hand reaches up: 1 (pinky), 2 (ring), 3 (middle), 4-5 (index)",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Letters and punctuation are yours. Now the number row - the figures that turn copy into fact: a date, a count, a page. We start with the left hand, digits 1 through 5. They live two rows up, so the real skill today is reaching the top row by feel and coming straight back home."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Each digit sits above the finger that already knows the column. 1 is the left pinky (above Q); 2 the ring; 3 the middle; 4 the index, straight up; 5 the same index, stretched up and to the right. Reach with one finger, tap, and return - the other fingers stay on the home row the whole time."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "⬆️",
      "title": "Reach, don't look",
      "text": "The numbers are a stretch, and that tempts the eyes downward. Don't. Feel your way up from each finger's letter and trust it. Lose your home position chasing a digit and you lose the next three keys too."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "1 2 3",
      "baseReps": 5,
      "keys": ["1", "2", "3"],
      "target": "1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Digits 1-2-3",
      "hint": "Pinky, ring, middle reach up in turn. Tap and bring the finger home."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "4 5",
      "baseReps": 8,
      "keys": ["4", "5"],
      "target": "4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5",
      "finger": "indigo",
      "title": "Digits 4-5",
      "hint": "Both are the left index: 4 straight up, 5 up and to the right."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Now mix the digits with letters, the way real text does - a label, a count, a quick tally. Type each chunk, then snap the hand back home. Read the line whole and keep your eyes on it, not on your fingers."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Numbers carry the facts. Get a digit wrong and you have not made a typo - you have changed the story.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "12 34 5 12345 a1 s2 d3 f4 g5 take 1 add 2 see 3 try 4 win 5",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Numbers with letters",
      "hint": "Reach up for the digit, return home, carry on. One space between groups."
    },
    {
